{
  "id": "unique-algorithm-001",
  "name": "Single-Day Volatility Breakout Detector",
  "description": "This strategy identifies single-day volatility contraction breakouts by scanning for days with the lowest True Range in the past 15 trading days. It places a bracket order the following day, buying at the previous day's high and selling at the previous day's low, to capitalize on potential price movements.",
  "algorithm_type": "TechnicalPattern",
  "prompt": "Design a strategy that detects \"single-day volatility contraction breakouts\" as follows:\n\n1. Scan for days where the True Range (High-Low) is both the lowest of the past 15 trading days AND less than 60% of the average True Range over that period.\n2. On the day after this contraction, place a bracket order:  \n   - Buy stop at the previous day's high  \n   - Sell stop at the previous day's low\n3. Whichever stop order is triggered becomes the trade direction. Once entered:\n   - Use a stop loss at the opposite side of the signal candle (previous day's low for long, high for short)\n   - Exit at either:\n     - 2x the True Range of the contraction candle in profit (take profit)\n     - Or after 3 trading days, whichever comes first\n4. Only one trade per asset at a time.  \n5. Ignore signals if overall 5-day average volume is below 75% of the 60-day average volume (to avoid illiquid periods).",
